jparsec.graph.chartRendering

Class TrajectoryElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • jparsec.graph.chartRendering.TrajectoryElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TrajectoryElement
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Support class for sky rendering operations, allowing to represent trajectory paths of Solar System objects or stars.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    T. Alonso Albi - OAN (Spain)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        Set apparent object name to be shown when rendering the sky.

        Initial Julian day of calculations in Barycentric dynamical time.

      • endTimeJD

        public double endTimeJD
        Ending Julian day of calculations in Barycentric dynamical time.

      • stepTimeJD

        public float stepTimeJD
        Sets Julian day step for calculations.

      • drawLabels

        public boolean drawLabels
        True if labels should be drawn. Dates will be refered to the same time scale used to define the rendering properties.

      • drawLabelsFormat

        public TrajectoryElement.LABELS drawLabelsFormat
        Sets the format of the labels according to the provided symbolic constants.

      • labelsSteps

        public int labelsSteps
        Sets number of steps between two consecutive drawn labels. Time step will be this value multiplied by the step time.

      • autoCentering

        public boolean autoCentering
        True if it is desirable to auto center the trajectory path. This overrides any other configuration in the sky render object.

      • autoScale

        public boolean autoScale
        True if it is desirable to auto scale the trajectory path. Auto scale operation is only performed when auto centering is enabled. This overrides any other configuration in the sky render object.

      • drawPathFont

        public Graphics.FONT drawPathFont
        Sets the font to be used for paths.

      • drawPathColor1

        public int drawPathColor1
        Sets the font color to be used for main paths.

      • drawPathColor2

        public int drawPathColor2
        Sets the font color to be used to highlight points in the paths with text labels.

      • showTimeScale

        public boolean showTimeScale
        True (default) to show the time scale. LT (local time) is not shown.

      • showTime

        public boolean showTime
        True (default) to show the time when it is not 0h or the interval between calculations is very little. Setting to false will also hide the time scale.

      • loc_path

        public LocationElement[] loc_path
        An array to store the equatorial positions of the object along the path.

      • central_loc

        public LocationElement central_loc
        Position at the center of the trajectory.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TrajectoryElement

        public TrajectoryElement()
        Default empty constructor.

      • TrajectoryElement

        public TrajectoryElement(RenderSky.OBJECT obj_type,
                 java.lang.String obj_name,
                 double JD_init,
                 double JD_end,
                 float JD_step,
                 boolean labels,
                 TrajectoryElement.LABELS labels_type,
                 int labels_step,
                 boolean auto_center,
                 boolean auto_scale)
                  throws JPARSECException
        Explicit constructor.
        Parameters:
        obj_type - Object type ID constant. Can be null to search it automatically (any object except probes and artificial satellites).
        obj_name - Object name.
        JD_init - Initial Julian day.
        JD_end - Ending Julian day.
        JD_step - Time step between calculations.
        labels - Show labels.
        labels_type - Type of labels.
        labels_step - Number of steps between two consecutive labels.
        auto_center - To automatically center the path.
        auto_scale - To automatically scale the render.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If the object type is unsupported.

      • populateTrajectoryPath

        public void populateTrajectoryPath(ObserverElement obs,
                          EphemerisElement eph)
                            throws JPARSECException
        Populates loc_path with the equatorial positions along the trajectory. In case the loc_path array is already populated this method does nothing.
        Parameters:
        obs - Observer object containing the observer position.
        eph - Ephemeris object defining the ephemeris properties.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

      • populateTrajectoryPath

        public void populateTrajectoryPath(LocationElement[] positions,
                          java.lang.String objName)
                            throws JPARSECException
        Populates loc_path with the equatorial positions provided as input, forcing the position of the object. This method is useful when you have ephemerides obtained with other tools.
        Parameters:
        positions - An array of positions. Its size should be equal at least to getNumberofPointsInTrajectory().
        objName - The name for the object when showing the label, or null to maintain the default one.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

      • getNumberofPointsInTrajectory

        public int getNumberofPointsInTrajectory()
        Returns the number of points to be calculated for the trajectory.
        Returns:
        Number of points.

      • setStarObject

        public void setStarObject(StarElement s)
        Sets the star object to be used to calculate its trajectory instead of having to read the entire star catalog and search for it. Default value is null to read the catalog, but for Android it is good to set it here so that performance is much better.
        Parameters:
        s - The star object, or null.
